        operation. Similarly, gas ovens may face issues with the gas supply, such as low pressure or leaks. These problems can
        lead to complete oven failure or intermittent operation, making it difficult to maintain consistent cooking schedules
        in a commercial setting. Regular inspection of electrical connections and gas lines, as well as ensuring that the
        power supply meets the oven’s requirements, are crucial steps in preventing power-related disruptions.</p>
      <p>7. <strong>Wear and Tear of Components</strong>: Commercial ovens are subject to heavy use, and over time, various
