        misaligned doors, difficulty in sliding racks, and inefficient air circulation within the oven. Such problems can
        affect the oven's performance and the quality of the food being cooked. Regular maintenance, including lubrication of
        moving parts, replacement of worn components, and periodic deep cleaning, can help extend the lifespan of the oven and
        maintain its efficiency.</p>
